		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">An investigation into quantum theory and quantum field theory in a space-time background having spatial defects (cosmic strings etc.)  will be carried out.  Particular emphasis will be paid to those defects arising from orbifold constructions on sphere.  The mode-problem, heat-kernal and functional determinant will be discussed for various equations of motion.  The calculation will be extended to arbitrary dimensions, and also to other defect codimensions, and information about heat-kernal coefficients extracted.  The system will be generalised by including a central magnetic monopole and the effect of the orbifolding on the Dirac quantization of monopole charge investigated.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
